Motaz A. Al-Mashouk has been vice president of engineering services at Saudi Aramco since April 1, 2022. Before this, he was executive director of engineering services, which he held since July 1, 2020. Throughout his 20-year career with the project management department at Aramco as manager and general manager, Al-Mashouk was responsible for executing a diverse portfolio of industrial projects, an iconic building and several infrastructure projects. Many were public-facing projects serving the broader interests of the Kingdom; several of them were accorded royal inauguration. These included King Abdullah University of Science and Technology, King Abdullah Petroleum Studies and Research Center, King Abdulaziz Center for World Culture and King Abdullah Sports City. His tenure with the project management department included leadership positions as general manager of Community Infrastructure and Public Projects, Public Service Project Management and Southern Area Project Management. Al-Mashouk also served as the manager of the Southern Area Projects Department, Project Support and Controls Department, and Project Management Office. Al-Mashouk’s earlier career with Aramco entailed professional and managerial assignments within the Engineering Services organization. Al-Mashouk holds a bachelor’s degree and a doctorate in science from the Imperial College of Science, Technology and Medicine, London, UK He also holds an MBA from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.